== 反應 ==

===提攜女性===
[[File:DowningStreetCatwalk.jpg|thumb]]
事前首相府已經放風指，內閣改組期間將會積極提攜女性，「多達十名」女性將加入內閣或初級政府。傳媒因而猜測男性大臣去向<ref name="The Telegraph">{{cite web|last1=Dominiczak|first1=Peter|title=David Cameron to promote young women to 'refresh' Cabinet|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/10964997/David-Cameron-to-promote-young-women-to-refresh-Cabinet.html|work=電訊報|accessdate=2016-06-28|archive-date=2020-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128073743/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/10964997/David-Cameron-to-promote-young-women-to-refresh-Cabinet.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，亦代表男性後座議員更難升官，更有指「如果你是男性白人，那麼你沒有機會升官」<ref name="telegraph.co.uk">{{cite web|last1=Ridge|first1=Sophy|title=Cameron's reshuffle: gender isn't the only thing women MPs have to offer|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/women/womens-politics/10966193/David-Cameron-Cabinet-reshuffle-2014-gender-isnt-all-women-MPs-have-to-offer.html|work=電訊報|accessdate=2016-06-29|archive-date=2020-10-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201027053446/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/women/womens-politics/10966193/David-Cameron-Cabinet-reshuffle-2014-gender-isnt-all-women-MPs-have-to-offer.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。這些消息令甘民樂在開始改組前就招致朝野批評，保守黨的{{tsl|en|Michael Ashcroft|米高·雅舒覺|雅舒覺勳爵}}認為「決定接下來的大臣改組會是輿論而非能力」<ref name="telegraph.co.uk"/>，工黨{{tsl|en|Shadow Home Secretary|影子內政大臣}}[[顧綺慧|顧綺慧]]批評這些任命是「臨急抱佛腳」，旨在[[2015年英國大選|明年春季大選]]前爭取女性選民支持<ref>{{cite web|last1=Press Association|title=Promotion of women in Tory reshuffle looks last-minute, says Labour|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/jul/13/promotion-women-cabinet-reshuffle-last-minute-labour-cooper-cameron|work=衛報|accessdate=2016-06-29|archive-date=2020-10-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201027035346/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/jul/13/promotion-women-cabinet-reshuffle-last-minute-labour-cooper-cameron|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
首相在改組期間擢升[[伊丽莎白·特拉斯|伊丽莎白·特拉斯]]，接替[[彭德森|彭德森]]出任環境大臣，更成為史上最年輕女性閣僚<ref name="telegraph.co.uk"/>；[[妮基·摩根|妮基·摩根]]入閣出任教育大臣；而現任就業國務大臣[[艾斯特·麦克维|艾斯特·麦克维]]和新任上議院領袖[[比斯頓女男爵蒂娜·斯托厄爾|蒂娜·斯托厄爾]]則可列席內閣會議。最終內閣17名保守黨人中有5名女性，所有保守黨大臣中有四分一是女性<ref name="condemned">{{cite web|last1=Mason|first1=Rowena|title=Daily Mail's 'Downing Street catwalk' condemned by MPs|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/jul/13/promotion-women-cabinet-reshuffle-last-minute-labour-cooper-cameron|date=2014-07-13|work=衛報|accessdate=2016-06-29|archive-date=2020-10-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201027035346/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/jul/13/promotion-women-cabinet-reshuffle-last-minute-labour-cooper-cameron|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

《[[每日郵報|每日郵報]]》翌日以「蔚宜-{zh-hk:美腿閃亮亮;zh-cn:大腿闪亮;zh-tw:大腿閃亮}-、唐寧街貓步之戰」為題，頭版報導是次內閣改組。其中在第四和五頁，報章插圖寫道「蔚宜：唐寧街貓步女皇」，又大篇幅附上多名女性前赴首相府時的照片，包括麥蔚宜、卓慧思、莫麗琪、司徒慧兒，以及新上任的初級大臣[[彭妮·莫当特|彭妮·莫当特]]、[[安珀·路德|安珀·路德]]、[[普丽蒂·帕特尔|普丽蒂·帕特尔]]、[[安娜·苏布里|安娜·苏布里]]和[[克莱尔·佩里|克莱尔·佩里]]。跨黨派的女政客紛紛出言批評或譴責報導的標題和圖片，保守黨的前威爾斯事務大臣[[謝麗爾·基蘭|謝麗爾·基蘭]]感到「震驚」，自民黨黨鞭{{tsl|en|Jenny Willott|珍妮·衛絡}}形容報導「駭人」，工黨議員{{tsl|en|Anne McGuire|安妮·麥桂}}批評報導等同美化「{{tsl|en|Blair Babe|貝理雅寶貝}}」。不過事件的主角麥蔚宜未有正面回應報導，只是說「獲邀出任其中一個最重要職位而感到高興」<ref name="condemned"/>。

=== 司徒氏被拒入閣 ===
[[比斯頓女男爵蒂娜·斯托厄爾|司徒慧兒]]成為有記憶之中首位[[上議院領袖|上議院領袖]]未能入閣後，旋即引起爭議。輿論普遍認為英揆是為了留位給[[夏偉林|夏偉林]]，惟他擔任的[[下議院領袖|下議院領袖]]通常不是內閣閣員<ref>{{cite web |title=Lords leader: Think of me as Beyonce |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-28547533 |website=BBC新聞 |accessdate=2020-07-29 |date=2014-07-29 |archive-date=2020-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201029142937/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-28547533 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[工党_(英国)|工黨]]以至保守黨貴族都批評此舉<ref>{{cite web |title=Cameron defends reshuffle changes |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-28321601 |website=BBC新聞 |accessdate=2020-07-29 |date=2014-07-16 |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112012504/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-28321601 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，隸屬執政黨的[[霍司富|霍司富勳爵]]直指，上議院領袖擁有閣僚職權是「重要」的<ref name="theguardian.com">{{cite web|last1=Watt|first1=Nicholas|title=Backbenchers rally to support Michael Gove after wife criticises reshuffle|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/jul/16/backbenchers-support-michael-gove-sarah-vine-protest|work=衛報|accessdate=2016-06-26|archive-date=2020-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201028015549/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/jul/16/backbenchers-support-michael-gove-sarah-vine-protest|dead-url=no}}</ref>。7月22日，甘民樂致函保守黨貴族協會主席{{tsl|en|Lord MacGregor of Pulham Market|麥傑嘉|佩咸市集的麥傑嘉勳爵}}，信中對司徒氏情況感到遺憾，提到上議院領袖「按慣例應為內閣閣員，但不幸地在此事上不可行」<ref>{{Cite hansard|column=1501|house=[[英國上議院|英國上議院]]|date=|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Lords/2014-07-28/debates/1407291000484/LeaderOfTheHouseOfLords#contribution-1407291000099|title=Leader of the House of Lords|access-date=2020-10-26|archive-date=2020-10-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201031071437/https://hansard.parliament.uk/Lords/2014-07-28/debates/1407291000484/LeaderOfTheHouseOfLords#contribution-1407291000099|dead-url=no}} {{Wayback|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Lords/2014-07-28/debates/1407291000484/LeaderOfTheHouseOfLords#contribution-1407291000099 |date=20201031071437 }}</ref>。{{tsl|en|Constitution Committee|憲法委員會 (英國)|上議院憲法委員會}}在後來的報告指出，「我國憲制核心在於大臣應從兩院制議會中被揀選，若任一院在內閣中不被代表，施政將舉步維艱<ref>{{cite web|title=Status of the Leader of the House of Lords|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld201415/ldselect/ldconst/41/4103.htm|accessdate=2016-06-26|publisher=上議院憲法委員會|archive-date=2020-09-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200906213512/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld201415/ldselect/ldconst/41/4103.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。」
工黨議員亦批評，司徒慧兒的年薪因未能入閣而比上任少22,000英鎊。保守黨決定代政府支付餘下薪金，但又隨即引起利益衝突之嫌，認為會影響上議院領袖執行職務。司徒氏最終拒絕保守黨的建議<ref>{{Cite news|title=Lords leader Baroness Stowell rejects Tory 'top-up' salary|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-28424394|newspaper=BBC新聞|date=2014-07-23|accessdate=2020-10-25|language=en-GB|archive-date=2020-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201110112515/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-28424394|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 彭德森遭到革職 ===
環境大臣[[彭德森|彭德森]]因應對夏季水災不力及呼籲捕殺[[獾|獾]]，而引起廣泛批評，最終遭到革職<ref name="The Independent">{{cite news | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/cabinet-reshuffle-a-newlook-team-that-david-cameron-hopes-will-keep-him-in-downing-street-9608347.html | location=London | work=獨立報 | title=Cabinet reshuffle: A new-look team that David Cameron hopes will keep him in Downing Street | date=2014-07-15 | accessdate=2020-10-26 | archive-date=2014-07-20 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140720195224/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/cabinet-reshuffle-a-newlook-team-that-david-cameron-hopes-will-keep-him-in-downing-street-9608347.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。據報彭氏警告首相，逼他離開政府會是「一大錯誤」，而保守黨的郊野支持者可能會改投[[英國獨立黨|英國獨立黨]]<ref>{{cite web|title=David Cameron's decision to sack Owen Paterson will send rural voters flooding to Ukip|url=http://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2014/07/8832941/|work=旁觀者|last1=Cash|first1=William|accessdate=2020-10-26|archive-date=2019-07-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190702233807/https://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2014/07/8832941/|dead-url=no}}</ref>；彭德森之後表示會繼續針對政府在多個範疇的施政<ref>{{cite web|title=Owen Patters On|url=http://order-order.com/2014/11/24/owen-patters-on/|publisher=Guido Fawkes|last1=Staines|first1=Paul|website=Guido Fawkes|accessdate=2020-10-26|archive-date=2020-10-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201031053921/https://order-order.com/2014/11/24/owen-patters-on/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。著名記者{{tsl|en|Christopher Booker|基斯托夫·博卡}}亦斥責甘民樂犯下任內最嚴重的錯誤，形容彭氏被革職是「侮辱郊野」<ref>{{cite web|last1=Booker|first1=Christopher|title=Sacking Owen Paterson is an insult to the countryside|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/earth/countryside/10977289/Sacking-Owen-Paterson-is-an-insult-to-the-countryside.html|work=電訊報|accessdate=2016-06-26|archive-date=2020-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128030010/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/earth/countryside/10977289/Sacking-Owen-Paterson-is-an-insult-to-the-countryside.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。有指政府是在環保團體、可再生能源公司和環保主義公務員的壓力下，才決定革職<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sparrow|first1=Andrew|title=I was sacked by David Cameron to appease 'the green blob', says Paterson|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/jul/20/owen-paterson-sacked-cabinet-appease-green-lobby|work=衛報|accessdate=2016-06-26|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111225532/http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/jul/20/owen-paterson-sacked-cabinet-appease-green-lobby|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

內閣改組後數日，彭氏被發現經常陪同[[霍理林|霍理林]]出入。曾任國防大臣的霍氏一度被認為有望回朝<ref name="The Telegraph"/>，但據報只獲提議出任[[外交、聯邦及發展事務部|外交部]]初級職位而感到「被羞辱」<ref name="theguardian.com"/>。甘民樂顧問擔心彭氏和霍氏將領導黨內反首相勢力，動搖他的地位<ref name="The Independent"/>。

===高文浩實際降職===
改組內閣前，保守黨首席競選策略師{{tsl|en|Lynton Crosby|連頓·郝彼}}警告甘民樂，教育大臣[[高文浩|高文浩]]會「毒害」選情。最終高氏被調任首席黨鞭，實際上等同降職<ref name="theguardian.com"/>。高氏妻子{{tsl|en|Sarah Vine|莎拉·范}}和特別顧問[[多米尼克·卡明斯|多米尼克·卡明斯]]都批評甘民樂向教育壓力團體「投降」<ref name="theguardian.com"/><ref name="https">{{cite web|last1=Watt|first1=Nicholas|title=David Cameron axes Michael Gove in reshuffle after toxic poll warning|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/jul/15/cameron-sacks-toxic-gove-promotes-women-reshuffle|work=衛報|accessdate=2016-06-27|archive-date=2020-10-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201027073044/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/jul/15/cameron-sacks-toxic-gove-promotes-women-reshuffle|dead-url=no}}</ref>。不過甘民樂讚揚高文浩「為國貢獻不凡」，解釋道「首席黨鞭是數一數二重要的政府職位」，強調「有能者居之」。甘相又指，新任黨鞭涉獵範圍將被過往更為廣泛，高文浩將在政府溝通戰略和保守黨競選兩方面，扮演重要角色<ref name="https"/><ref>{{cite web|last1=Simons|first1=Ned|title=Michael Gove Sacked As Education Secretary in Dramatic Reshuffle|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2014/07/15/michael-gove-reshuffle-chief-whip_n_5586854.html|work=哈芬登郵報|accessdate=2016-06-27|archive-date=2017-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170623063631/http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2014/07/15/michael-gove-reshuffle-chief-whip_n_5586854.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。高氏亦拒絕形容調職屬降級，縱使因突然離任教育大臣而難受，但對「進入政府核心任職感到興奮」<ref>{{cite web|title=Michael Gove move not a demotion, says David Cameron|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-28302487|publisher=BBC新聞|accessdate=2016-06-27|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112010133/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-28302487|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 許晉帆駐任歐盟 ===
不太知名的{{tsl|en|Jonathan Hill, Baron Hill of Oareford|俄福的許晉帆男爵}}在今次改組中獲任命為英國的[[歐盟委員會專員|歐盟委員會專員]]，卻遭到國內和歐洲大陸的批評。改組前，外界相信歐盟專員一職會由前衛生大臣[[安德鲁·兰斯利|安德鲁·兰斯利]]、或前首席黨鞭[[安德魯·米切爾|安德魯·米切爾]]、或已退休的大學國務大臣[[韋力生|韋力生]]、又或前保守黨黨魁[[迈克尔·霍华德|迈克尔·霍华德]]接任<ref name="The Telegraph"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Lord Jonathan Hill of Oareford: from Lord Who? to EU commissioner|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/sep/10/lord-jonathan-hill-oareford-eu-commissioner|accessdate=2016-06-27|work=衛報|last1=Mason|first1=Rowena|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111213643/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/sep/10/lord-jonathan-hill-oareford-eu-commissioner|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="BBC News">{{cite web|title=Lord Hill set to become UK's new EU Commissioner|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-28310707|accessdate=2016-06-27|publisher=BBC新聞|archive-date=2020-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101164435/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-28310707|dead-url=no}}</ref>。改組前一個月，許氏更認為此職位是「不情願的徵召」，對此「沒有、沒有、沒有」興趣<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gimson|first1=Andrew|title=Lord Hill denies he will be our next European Commissioner, and draws lessons for 2015 from the victory of 1992|url=http://www.conservativehome.com/highlights/2014/06/lord-hill-denies-he-will-be-our-next-european-commissioner-and-draws-lessons-for-2015-from-the-victory-of-1992.html|website=Conservative Home|publisher=Conservative Home|accessdate=2016-06-27|archive-date=2020-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030064030/https://www.conservativehome.com/highlights/2014/06/lord-hill-denies-he-will-be-our-next-european-commissioner-and-draws-lessons-for-2015-from-the-victory-of-1992.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。不單新上任的不情願，就連新任委員會主席[[让-克洛德·容克|让-克洛德·容克]]本來也希望是高知名度或女性出任專員，外界擔心英方或因而被忽視<ref>{{cite web|last1=Pop|first1=Valentina|title=Juncker Wants More Women in EU Commission Reshuffle|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/brussels/2015/04/24/juncker-wants-more-women-in-eu-commission-reshuffle/|work=華爾街日報|accessdate=2016-06-27|archive-date=2016-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161010123948/http://blogs.wsj.com/brussels/2015/04/24/juncker-wants-more-women-in-eu-commission-reshuffle/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
[[英國獨立黨|英國獨立黨]]黨魁[[奈杰尔·法拉奇|奈杰尔·法拉奇]]嘲諷許晉帆「你是誰」，又批評他完全沒有能力重新談判<ref>{{cite web|last1=Cisp|first1=James|title=Cameron names pro-EU lord who didn't want the job as Commissioner|url=http://www.euractiv.com/section/uk-europe/news/cameron-names-pro-eu-lord-who-didn-t-want-the-job-as-commissioner/|publisher=EurActiv|accessdate=2016-06-27|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112012248/https://www.euractiv.com/section/uk-europe/news/cameron-names-pro-eu-lord-who-didn-t-want-the-job-as-commissioner/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。{{tsl|en|Open Europe|開放歐洲}}總監{{tsl|en|Mats Persson|麥斯·皮申}}亦攻擊是次任命，擔心其他國家會派出皇牌到布魯塞爾，最終會令到英方擔任歐盟委員會關鍵職位，例如內部市場、競爭或貿易的機會更加渺茫<ref name="BBC News"/>。許晉帆的提名聽證會亦非一帆風順。[[欧洲议会|欧洲议会]]的左翼議員認為他與[[倫敦市|倫敦市]]過於緊密，因而需要出席第二場聽證會，期間許氏被形容為「有魅力但內裡空洞」<ref>{{cite web|title=UK's Lord Hill recalled for more questioning by MEPs|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-29442089|publisher=BBC新聞|accessdate=2016-06-27|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112031831/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-29442089|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他的提名最終獲通過，並留任至[[英國去留歐盟公投|英國去留歐盟公投]]後。

===被革職後獲晉爵===
{{tsl|en|Department for International Development|國際發展部}}[[阿蘭·鄧肯|阿蘭·鄧肯]]、外交部{{tsl|en|Hugh Robertson (politician)|曉·羅拔臣}}和[[英格蘭及威爾斯副檢察長|副律政司]][[奧利弗·赫德|奧利弗·赫德]]被革職後獲甘民樂晉升為爵士，前兩者成為[[聖米迦勒及聖喬治勳章|聖米迦勒及聖喬治勳章]]二等勳爵士，後者則為[[下級勳位爵士|下級勳位爵士]]。工黨的[[柴萍恩|柴萍恩]]批評，晉爵男性比起閣內女性還要多，且只有男校舊生受惠，就可見甘民樂變得多麼離地<ref>{{cite web|last1=Murphy|first1=Joe|title=PM accused of abuse of honours system as 'shuffled' ministers are put up for knighthoods|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/david-cameron-honours-system-abuse-reshuffle-knighthoods-9609014.html|work=倫敦旗幟晚報|accessdate=2016-06-29|archive-date=2020-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201028015549/https://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/david-cameron-honours-system-abuse-reshuffle-knighthoods-9609014.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。至於作為現代史中任職閣僚時間最長之一的[[祁淦禮|祁淦禮]]獲頒[[名譽勳位|名譽勳位]]，外界大多不貶只褒，惟獨工黨的{{tsl|en|Stephen Pound|史提芬·彭}}批評「無意批評長期服務獎，但用勳位去止離職之痛就好比濫藥」。甘民樂回應時引用前[[蘇格蘭皇家銀行|蘇格蘭皇家銀行]]行政總裁{{tsl|en|Fred Goodwin|費德·古溫}}為例，提及他雖形象敗壞卻仍在2004年獲[[托尼·布莱尔|托尼·布莱尔]]晉爵，譏諷工黨沒資格說教<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hope|first1=Christopher|title=David Cameron criticised over plans to knight Tory victims of reshuffle|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/10971725/David-Cameron-criticised-over-plans-to-knight-Tory-victims-of-reshuffle.html|work=電訊報|accessdate=2016-06-29|archive-date=2020-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128073746/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/10971725/David-Cameron-criticised-over-plans-to-knight-Tory-victims-of-reshuffle.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

